node.text:
This is how I choose to remember Cerain. Vibrant. Fun. He came to Hawaii with us to on the last Real Comedians tour. He hiked, biked, helped out. Such a great kid. He hung out at so many Keep Your Distance shows. He loved comedy. He loved his dad. He looked up to him and I loved to see how he looked at Tone. 
I love Tony’s boys like my own. 

I look up to Tony in a lot of ways as a father.  He helps me thru the transition of my kids turning their backs on me.  Everything I go thru he’s been thru.  His pain is my pain. His grief is my grief. I wouldn’t wish this on my worst enemy. Much less my friend. So tragic.  Praying for the Baker family. Cencere. Sabrina. Mama Sandy. Their mother.  All the family friends of the others lost. Life is cruel. Life moves on and that seems to be the cruelest part of all. 

What is grief, if not love persevering? To lose someone we have lost does not erase the love we have felt for them, it simply moves the object of our love out of reach.

🕊🕊🕊
